2026-03-21 | Flip K×K Submatrix Vertically

	Question
Return the updated matrix after flipping the specified submatrix.

	Approach
1.	Identify the submatrix:
		rows → x to x+k-1  
		columns → y to y+k-1  

2.	Use two pointers:
		top = x  
		bottom = x + k - 1  

3.	While top < bottom:
		swap entire rows within column range [y, y+k-1]

4.	Move:
		top++  
		bottom--  

5.	Return modified grid.

	Time Complexity
	O(k²)

	Space Complexity
	O(1)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> flipSubmatrix(vector<vector<int>>& grid, int x, int y, int k) {

        int top = x;
        int bottom = x + k - 1;

        while (top < bottom) {

            for (int col = y; col < y + k; col++) {
                swap(grid[top][col], grid[bottom][col]);
            }

            top++;
            bottom--;
        }

        return grid;
    }
};

	Key Insight
We only reverse rows inside the square region.  
This is equivalent to reversing a subarray of rows but only within a fixed column range.
